{"id":"category--distance-to-vor","title":"Distance to VOR","count":23,"selectionType":"category","questions":[{"index":0,"uid":"2025_regionals:30","number":"30","question":"An aircraft DME (which is a slant range) shows 4.8 nm. If the aircraft is at 15,000' MSL and the station is at sea level, what is the horizontal distance between them?","choices":[{"letter":"A","text":"3.87 nm"},{"letter":"B","text":"4.12 nm"},{"letter":"C","text":"4.43 nm"},{"letter":"D","text":"4.68 nm"}],"answerKey":"B","correctChoice":"4.12 nm","answerKeyType":"Right Triangle Math","questionType":"multiple_choice","context":"","table":null,"category":"Distance to VOR","sourceTestId":"2025_regionals","sourceTestTitle":"2025 Regionals","sourceYear":2025,"sourceEvent":"regionals","referenceScope":"2025_regionals"},{"index":1,"uid":"2024_regionals:4","number":"4","question":"You cross 16 radials in 12.6 minutes. Your airspeed on an arc is 208 km/hr. How far are you from the VOR station?","choices":[{"letter":"A","text":"537,401 feet"},{"letter":"B","text":"191,304 yards"},{"letter":"C","text":"166,720 meters"},{"letter":"D","text":"26.4 kilometers"}],"answerKey":"A","correctChoice":"537,401 feet","answerKeyType":"","questionType":"multiple_choice","context":"","table":null,"category":"Distance to VOR","sourceTestId":"2024_regionals","sourceTestTitle":"2024 Regionals","sourceYear":2024,"sourceEvent":"regionals","referenceScope":"2024_regionals"},{"index":2,"uid":"2023_regionals:7","number":"7","question":"At FL360 conventional DME indicates a slant range of 12 nm. How many nautical miles laterally are you truly from the station?","choices":[{"letter":"A","text":"8.5"},{"letter":"B","text":"9.5"},{"letter":"C","text":"10.5"},{"letter":"D","text":"11.5"}],"answerKey":"C","correctChoice":"10.5","answerKeyType":"","questionType":"multiple_choice","context":"","table":null,"category":"Distance to VOR","sourceTestId":"2023_regionals","sourceTestTitle":"2023 Regionals","sourceYear":2023,"sourceEvent":"r